Name: AssertionResponseTypes

Name: BundleType
Title: BundleType

Name: CarePlanIntent
Title: Care Plan Intent
Description: Codes indicating the degree of authority/intentionality associated with a care plan.

Name: CodeSearchSupport
Title: CodeSearchSupport
Description: The degree to which the server supports the code search parameter on ValueSet, if it is supported.

Name: CompartmentType
Title: CompartmentType
Description: Which type a compartment definition describes.

Name: CompositionStatus
Title: CompositionStatus
Description: The workflow/clinical status of the composition.

Name: ConsentState
Title: ConsentState
Description: Indicates the state of the consent.

Name: DataType
Title: DataType
Description: A version specific list of the data types defined by the FHIR specification for use as an element  type (any of the FHIR defined data types).

Name: DeviceUseStatementStatus
Title: DeviceUseStatementStatus
Description: A coded concept indicating the current status of the Device Usage.

Name: DiscriminatorType
Title: DiscriminatorType
Description: How an element value is interpreted when discrimination is evaluated.

Name: DocumentRelationshipType
Title: DocumentRelationshipType
Description: The type of relationship between documents.

Name: EncounterStatus
Title: EncounterStatus
Description: Current state of the encounter.

Name: EndpointPayloadType
Title: Endpoint Payload Type
Description: This is an example value set defined by the FHIR project, that could be used to represent possible payload document types.

Name: EventTiming
Title: EventTiming
Description: Real world event relating to the schedule.

Name: FilterOperator
Title: FilterOperator
Description: The kind of operation to perform as a part of a property based filter.

Name: GroupType
Title: GroupType
Description: Types of resources that are part of group.

Name: IssueSeverity
Title: IssueSeverity
Description: How the issue affects the success of the action.

Name: IssueType
Title: IssueType
Description: A code that describes the type of issue.

Name: QuestionnaireItemType
Title: QuestionnaireItemType
Description: Distinguishes groups from questions and display text and indicates data type for questions.

Name: CommonLanguages
Title: Common Languages
Description: This value set includes common codes from BCP-47 (http://tools.ietf.org/html/bcp47)

Name: MediaType
Title: Media Type
Description: Codes for high level media categories.

Name: EntityNamePartQualifier
Title: EntityNamePartQualifier
Description: A set of codes each of which specifies a certain subcategory of the name part in addition to the main name part type.

Name: NamingSystemIdentifierType
Title: NamingSystemIdentifierType
Description: Identifies the style of unique identifier used to identify a namespace.

Name: ObservationInterpretationCodes
Title: Observation Interpretation Codes
Description: A categorical assessment, providing a rough qualitative interpretation of the observation value,    such as “normal”/ “abnormal”,”low” / “high”, “better” / “worse”, “susceptible” / “resistant”, “expected”/ “not expected”.    The value set is intended to be for ANY use where coded representation of an interpretation is needed.             Notes:          This is being communicated in v2.x in OBX-8 (Observation Interpretation), in v3 in ObservationInterpretation (CWE) in R1 (Representative Realm) and in FHIR in    Observation.interpretation. Historically these values come from the laboratory domain, and these codes are extensively    used. The value set binding is extensible, so codes outside the value set that are needed for interpretation concepts    (i.e. particular meanings) that are not included in the value set can be used, and these new codes may also be added to    the value set and published in a future version.

Name: ObservationStatus
Title: ObservationStatus
Description: Codes providing the status of an observation.

Name: ParticipationStatus
Title: ParticipationStatus
Description: The Participation status of an appointment.

Name: ProvenanceEntityRole
Title: ProvenanceEntityRole
Description: How an entity was used in an activity.

Name: QuantityComparator
Title: QuantityComparator
Description: How the Quantity should be understood and represented.

Name: RelatedArtifactType
Title: RelatedArtifactType
Description: The type of relationship to the related artifact.

Name: SearchModifierCode
Title: SearchModifierCode
Description: A supported modifier for a search parameter.

Name: StudyType
Title: StudyType
Description: Types of research studies (types of research methods).

Name: SubscriptionStatus
Title: SubscriptionStatus
Description: The status of a subscription.

Name: SupplyItemType
Title: Supply Item Type
Description: This value sets refers to a specific supply item.

Name: TestScriptOperationCode
Title: Test script operation code
Description: This value set defines a set of codes that are used to indicate the supported operations of a testing engine or tool.

Name: Common UCUM units
Description: Commonly encountered UCUM units (for purposes of helping populate look ups.

Name: UDIEntryType
Title: UDIEntryType
Description: Codes to identify how UDI data was entered.

Name: status
Title: Status
Description: The validation status of the target
